ConflictStatus Enum

In this Article

Specifies whether any changes were made to a merged PrintTicket to ensure a viable PrintTicket.

Syntax

Declaration

[System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComVisible(false)]
public enum ConflictStatus

Inheritance Hierarchy

  • Object
  • ValueType
  • System.Enum
  • ConflictStatus

Remarks

When the <xref:System.Printing.PrintQueue.MergeAndValidatePrintTicket%2A> method merges two PrintTicket objects, the initial print ticket may request printing functions that the printer does not support. In such cases, the printer driver changes the non-viable settings to ensure that the final print ticket is viable. The <xref:System.Printing.PrintQueue.MergeAndValidatePrintTicket%2A> method uses this enumeration to report whether it had to make changes to ensure a viable print ticket.

Fields

ConflictResolved

One or more conflicts were found and all conflicts were resolved.
NoConflict

No conflicts were found between the initial merged print ticket and the supported printer functions.
